  "body": "The 2.3 documentation site puts related contracts together in the same page, divided according to some categorization. For example [Crowdsale contracts](https://v2-3-0-rc-1--openzeppelin-docs-next.netlify.com/api/crowdsale) are divided according to what they affect: emission, price, validation, or distribution. [ERC20 contracts](https://v2-3-0-rc-1--openzeppelin-docs-next.netlify.com/api/token/erc20) are dividided in interfaces, contracts, and utilities.\r\n\r\n@Aniket-Engg pointed out in https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/solidity-docgen/issues/23#issuecomment-485655382 that this is inconsistent. Moreover, most of the other contracts are in a catch-all \"Contracts\" category which is not useful. This issue is about adding good categories to all directories. For how this is done see the [ERC20 `README.md`](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-solidity/blame/ed5652b/contracts/token/ERC20/README.md) as an example.\r\n\r\n\r\nIn the case of ERC20 for example I think it would make sense to have a \"Core\" category with the `IERC20` interface and core `ERC20` contract, perhaps also `ERC20Detailed`. Then we can have an \"Extensions\" category with `ERC20Mintable`, etc. If there are several extensions related to the same thing, like with crowdsales, they could go in their own category.",
